commentTextItems.html: An anticlimactic end to a game that was in Afghanistan's control from the three-quarter point of the Hong Kong innings, 216 was unlikely to be enough on a slow but true batting surface. Afghanistan's bowlers all did well, Mirwais the pick with 0-25 off his 10 overs, Hamza and Nabi taking 5-55 off their combined 20. Afghanistan's debutant and Man of the Match Usman Ghani played some audacious strokes on his way to 70 off 68 and with Hong Kong dropping five catches, Afghanistan raced away with the game.

milestones.description: Skhawat Ali and Irfan Ahmed's 60-run partnership is HKG's highest for the 1st wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 27 between Tabarak Dar and Skhawat Ali
Nizakat Khan and Babar Hayat's 48-run partnership is HKG's highest for the 4th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 13 between Hussain Butt and Zain Abbas
Babar Hayat and Ankur Vasishta's 34-run partnership is HKG's highest for the 6th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 24 between Roy Lamsam and Irfan Ahmed
Samiullah Shinwari has scored 5 fifty-plus scores in ODIs, the most for AFG breaking Shahzad's record
Babar Hayat's 53 is the highest individual score in ODIs (for HKG), surpassing Tabarak Dar's 36
Babar Hayat has broken the record for most runs in boundaries (36) in an innings in ODIs for HKG, going past Tabarak Dar's 24
Skhawat Ali and Irfan Ahmed's 60-run partnership is HKG's highest for any wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 50 between Tabarak Dar and French
Atkinson has broken the record for most dismissals (3) in ODIs for HKG, going past Tim Smart's 2
Irfan Ahmed has broken the record for most sixes in an innings (2) in ODIs for HKG, going past Manoj Cheruparambil's 1
Dawlat Zadran has broken the record for most ducks (3) in ODIs for AFG, going past Shapoor's 3
Mohammad Nabi has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (32) for AFG, going past Samiullah Shinwari
